abstract: Meb Keflezighi plans to run the New York City Marathon on Nov 6, his first of the year, then compete in the Olympic trials marathon 10 weeks later; no other American expected to qualify for United States team will attempt both races.
snippet: Meb Keflezighi plans to run both the New York City Marathon on Nov. 6 and the United States Olympic trials 10 weeks later, but many other top Americans will run only the trials.
lead_paragraph: Meb Keflezighi plans to run both the New York City Marathon on Nov. 6 and the United States Olympic trials 10 weeks later, but many other top Americans will run only the trials.

headline.main: Two Marathons in Two Months Is Too Much for Many
headline.print_headline: For Many Top Americans, Two Marathons in Two Months Is Too Much
headline.seo: Many Top Americans Will Run Olympic Marathon Trials, Not New York
